which there\nare two random variables $X^0, X^1$ supported on $\\{0, \\dots ,m\\}$ such that\n(i) the total variation distance between $X^0$ and $X^1$ is at least\n$1-\\gamma$, and (ii) the moment generating functions of $X^0$ and $X^1$ are\nwithin a constant factor of each other everywhere? We show that the answer is\n$m = \\Theta(\\sqrt{\\log(1/\\gamma)})$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 5 Feb 2020 18:53:21 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-02-06"}
