{"id":"2002.01922","submitter":"Tristan Collins","authors":"Jianchun Chu, Tristan C. Collins, Man-Chun Lee","title":"The space of almost calibrated $(1,1)$ forms on a compact K\\\"ahler\n  manifold","comments":"50 pages","journal-ref":"Geom. Topol. 25 (2021) 2573-2619","doi":"10.2140/gt.2021.25.2573","report-no":null,"categories":"math.DG math.SG","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  The space $\\mathcal{H}$ of \"almost calibrated\" $(1,1)$ forms on a compact\nK\\\"ahler manifold plays an important role in the study of the deformed\nHermitian-Yang-Mills equation of mirror symmetry as emphasized by recent work\nof the second author and Yau, and is related by mirror symmetry to the space of\npositive Lagrangians studied by Solomon. This paper initiates the study of the\ngeometry of $\\mathcal{H}$. We show that $\\mathcal{H}$ is an infinite\ndimensional Riemannian manifold with non-positive sectional curvature. In the\nhypercritical phase case we show that $\\mathcal{H}$ has a well-defined metric\nstructure, and that its completion is a ${\\rm CAT}(0)$ geodesic metric space,\nand hence has an intrinsically defined ideal boundary. Finally, we show that in\nthe hypercritical phase case $\\mathcal{H}$ admits $C^{1,1}$ geodesics,\nimproving a result of the second author and Yau. Using results of\nDarvas-Lempert we show that this result is sharp.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 5 Feb 2020 18:56:13 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-09-15"}
