 which, if detected, might then be interpreted as a\nsign that TRAPPIST-1b and TRAPPIST-1c could have a liquid magma ocean. For\nTRAPPIST-1 and similar systems, the models to fit the TTVs should potentially\naccount for general relativity, for the tidal deformation of the planets, for\nthe rotational deformation of the planets and, to a lesser extent, for the\nrotational deformation of the star, which would add up to 7x2+1 = 15 additional\nfree parameters in the case of TRAPPIST-1.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 5 Feb 2020 22:10:44 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-03-25"}
