sponding to a methyl\nmigration leading to a Mg-CH$_3$OH$^+$ complex, though only if this transition\nstate is stabilized significantly relative to the dissociated MgOH$^+$ + CH$_3$\nproduct channel. An alternative non-statistical mechanism is discussed, whereby\na post-transition state bifurcation in the potential surface could allow the\nreaction to proceed directly from the four-centered TS to the Mg-CH$_3$OH$^+$\ncomplex thereby allowing a more robust competition between the product\nchannels.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 6 Feb 2020 08:19:54 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-06-24"}
