ults, and the systematic\nerrors are basically within 300 G. In addition, we find that there are many\n\"bright spots\" and \"dark spots\" on the inclination angle images from the\ninversion results of \\textit{Hinode}/SP with values of 180 and 0 degrees,\nrespectively, where the inversion is not reliable and does not produce a good\nresult; the MagMLP handles these points well.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 6 Feb 2020 13:31:33 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-02-07"}
